From these data of observations, we knew effects of climate change in environment and water resources. But how Earth's water cycle is actually affected? how these things can leads to water scarcity?... Due to increase in temperature rate of evaporation increases, which can lead some small water resources like lakes, ponds, small rivers to dry and also change the rain pattern. There is also decrease in underground water level. This leads to altered percipitation which results in more rainfall in some places and drought in other place. It disturb timing and distribution of water resource.which ultimaltely affect natural water cycle. And drought and drying of water resources leads to water crisis. Ice-caps are one of major source of fresh water due to melting of ice-caps and snow in large amount there will be water crisis in dry seasons. And also rise in sea level. Due to increased sea level salt water mix with fresh water source in coastal region making it unfit for drinking and irrigation. Temperature difference between places due to climate change can also change wind patern.  · 6 m
